Privacy Policy and Terms
Privacy Policy for Greed City
Last Updated: 16 September 2024
Lighthouse Games Studio ("we", "our", or "us") operates the mobile game "Greed City" (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the App. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By accessing or using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
1.
Information We Collect
Information from Facebook Login
: When you log in using Facebook, we collect your public profile information (e.g., name, email address, profile picture). We do not collect your Facebook Friends list.
Gameplay Data
: Includes in-game actions, achievements, game progress, and anti-cheat data.
Device Information
: Includes device type, operating system, IP address, and unique device identifiers. We do not collect mobile network information.
Location Data
: We collect location data when you check in to businesses. This is only used for gameplay and is not revealed to other players.
Analytics and Crash Data
: Collected through Unity Analytics and Firebase to improve performance and monitor crashes.
Purchase Information
: Managed by Google Play Store and Apple Game Center. We do not store payment details but collect purchase history for account management.
2.
How We Use Your Information
User Management
: Authenticate users and manage accounts.
Gameplay Experience
: Track game progress, detect cheating, and personalize gameplay.
Notifications
: Send push notifications via Firebase for game updates and promotional content.
Improvements
: Use collected data to enhance and improve the App’s features.
3.
Data Sharing
Service Providers
: Unity Analytics and Firebase are used to track game performance.
Social Platforms
: Data may be shared with Facebook for login purposes.
Legal Requirements
: We may disclose data if required by law.
4.
User Control
Account Deletion
: You can delete your account by navigating to
Menu > Settings > Account Deletion
within the App.
Opt-out of Notifications
: Disable push notifications via your device settings.
Disconnect Facebook
: Disconnect Facebook from your App via Facebook settings.
5.
Data Retention
We retain your data as long as your account is active or as required for legal compliance. Upon request, your data will be deleted.
6.
Security
We implement appropriate security measures to protect your data but cannot guarantee complete security.
7.
Children's Privacy
The App is not directed at children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided personal information, we will delete it.
8.
International Data Transfers
Your data may be processed outside of your home country. By using the App, you consent to such processing.
9.
Changes to the Privacy Policy
We may update this policy periodically. Changes will be communicated through the App, and continued use will indicate acceptance.
10.
Contact Us
Lighthouse Games Studio
Egham Court, Grove Rd,
London, United Kingdom
Email: [Insert Contact Email]
Terms & Conditions for Greed City
Last Updated: [Insert Date]
1.
Copyright Infringement
Greed City is not responsible for user-provided content (e.g., images, comments) that may infringe on copyrights or trademarks. To report offending material, email us at
contact@LighthouseGamesStudio.com
.
2.
Offensive Material
Usernames, images, and business names deemed offensive will be removed upon request. Greed City reserves the right to delete offending content or accounts. Report offensive content by emailing
contact@greed-city.com
.
3.
Geolocation
Location data is collected for gameplay purposes (e.g., check-ins). Your exact location is never disclosed to other players. Geolocation data is only collected when you manually check in at businesses.
4.
Gameplay Disclaimer
Greed City may terminate any account without compensation for purchased digital items. We are not liable for data loss, temporary unavailability, or any indirect damages resulting from the use of the App.
5.
Limitation of Liability
To the fullest extent permitted by law, Greed City, its directors, employees, and partners are not liable for any indirect or consequential losses, including loss of profits, data, or goodwill. Total liability is limited to $100 or the minimum required by applicable law.
6.
Content Accuracy
Greed City is not responsible for the accuracy or completeness of user-submitted business names, locations, or gameplay data. This information is provided for gameplay purposes only and does not reflect real-world business conditions.
7.
Policy Towards Children
Our services are not directed to individuals under 13. If we learn that we have collected data from a child under 13, we will delete it immediately and terminate the account. If you become aware that your child has provided personal information, please contact us at
contact@LighthouseGamesStudio.com
.
8.
Deleting Personal Information
You can request the deletion of your personal data through
Menu > Settings > Account Deletion
within the App. Alternatively, email us at
contact@LighthouseGamesStudio.com
.
9.
User-Generated Content
Businesses, comments, and images submitted by players are the responsibility of the user. Greed City reserves the right to remove any content deemed inappropriate.
10.
Limitation for European and Australian Users
For users in the European Economic Area (EEA) and Australia, liability for death, personal injury, fraud, or other mandatory legal obligations cannot be excluded or limited.
